articles.description: From the immortal locks to the veterans with work left to do to the under-24 players that already appear on track, here are our picks.
articles.headline: Which current NHL players will make the Hockey Hall of Fame?

images.name: Makar, MacKinnon [1296x729]
images.alt: Colorado Avalanche defenseman Cale Makar (8) and Colorado Avalanche center Nathan MacKinnon (29) wait for teammates to celebrate Makars goal in the third period against the Arizona Coyotes at Ball Arena March 24, 2023.
images.credit: Andy Cross/MediaNews Group/The Denver Post via Getty Images

images.name: Crosby Ovechkin [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: Sidney Crosby and Alex Ovechkin have had iconic careers in the sport.

images.name: Evgeni Malkin [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: Though Evgeni Malkin's name isn't always included on massive "best of" lists, his career accomplishments will land him in the Hall early on in his eligibility.
images.credit: Jeanine Leech/Icon Sportswire via Getty Images

images.name: Auston Matthews [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: There will come a time perhaps not too far down the road where we consider Auston Matthews a shoo-in for the Hall of Fame.

images.name: Doughty [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: Drew Doughty is easily one of the most recognizable faces in the NHL, and has been a model of consistent excellency in the league and international play.

images.name: Burns bag [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: Brent Burns has put up an astounding number of points in his career -- and is also quite a character.

images.name: Jack Eichel [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: "Playoff Jack Eichel" was a force to be reckoned with during the Golden Knights' path to the Cup last spring.

images.name: Jonathan Quick [608x342]
images.alt: Jonathan Quick #32 of the Los Angeles Kings holds up the Stanley Cup after the Kings defeated the New Jersey Devils 6-1 to win the Stanley Cup series 4-2 in Game Six of the 2012 Stanley Cup Final at Staples Center on June 11, 2012 in Los Angeles, Californ
images.caption: Jonathan Quick won two Cups during his tenure with the Kings.
